com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetSearchResultsResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianResponse
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetSearchResultsResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataProvider, RecordsProvider, Serializable

    public class GetSearchResultsResponse
extends SiperianResponse
implements RecordsProvider, DataProvider
    Response to a GetSearchResultsRequest.

    The response contains an ArrayList of records associated with the search token specified by GetSearchResultsRequest.setSearchToken(String). The first records to return as well as the number of records to return are also specified in the GetSearchResultsRequest.

    The code below shows how to print out the records in a GetSearchResultsResponse:

    Usage Example:

    GetSearchResultsResponse response = new GetSearchResultsResponse();
    int i=0;
    for(Iterator iter=response.getRecords().iterator(); iter.hasNext();)
    { //iterate through response records
     System.out.println("Printing response record " + i);
     Record record = (Record) iter.next();
     Collection fields = record.getFields();
     for(Iterator fieldIter=fields.iterator(); fieldIter.hasNext();)
    { //iterate through rest of fields
     Field f = (Field) fieldIter.next();
     System.out.println(f.getName() + ": " + f.getValue());
     }
    }
    See Also:
    GetSearchResultsRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetSearchResultsRequest

    API Group: Data Retrieval
